slations":{"at":1772469958006,"data":{"id":5975181,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"李乘风","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"李乘風","primary":false}}]}},"tv_281233_keywords":{"at":1772469960580,"data":{"id":281233,"results":[{"name":"donghua","id":315535},{"name":"based on web novel","id":318933}]}},"tv_109441_keywords":{"at":1772469961308,"data":{"id":109441,"results":[]}},"person_65971_translations":{"at":1772469961885,"data":{"id":65971,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Shih Kien (Chinese: 石堅, 1 January 1913 – 3 June 2009), also known as Shek Wing-cheung, Sek Gin, or Shek Kin, was a Hong Kong–based Chinese actor and martial artist. He was born on January 1, 1913 in Shigang, Guangzhou, China and died on June 3, 2009 in Hong Kong.\n\nSek Kin began his career in the film industry in 1939 as a make-up artist. He made his acting debut in 1940 with the film \"Flower in a Sea of Blood\". In the 1950s and 1960s, he became well-known for his roles as villains in kung fu films. He appeared in many popular films of this era, including the \"Wong Fei Hung\" series, the \"Fong Sai Yuk\" series, and \"Buddha's Palm\".\n\nIn 1973, Sek Kin starred opposite Bruce Lee in the film \"Enter the Dragon\". He played the role of Han, the main villain of the film. Sek Kin's performance in \"Enter the Dragon\" was critically acclaimed and he is considered to be one of the greatest villains in kung fu cinema.\n\nIn the 1970s and 1980s, Sek Kin continued to act in both films and television series. He also began to work as a production manager on films. In 1996, he was honored with the Lifetime Achievement Award of the Hong Kong Film Critics' Association. In 2003, he was given the Professional Achievement Award at the Hong Kong Film Awards.\n\nSek Kin died on June 3, 2009 at the age of 96. He was a highly respected actor who made a significant contribution to the Hong Kong film industry. He is remembered for his iconic roles as villains in kung fu films and for his groundbreaking work in the early days of Hong Kong cinema.","name":"Sek Kin","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"石坚（1913年1月1日－2009年6月3日），原名石荣璋，籍贯广东番禺石岗村，香港粤语电影演员，电影、电视作品无数。另有外号奸人坚，是粤语电影中的老牌反派，经常都在黄飞鸿电影里担任反派的角色。\n\n　　石坚从小被二妈养大，少年时体弱多病，故习武以强身健体，一学九年，习鹰爪、螳螂、罗汉、少林、山西朝元派和保定快跤等门派功夫，因此建立起功夫底子，为日后的演艺生涯竖立基础。适逢抗日战争爆发，学生时期的石坚积极投入罢课抗战，联袂友人筹划抗日话剧，纵横省港两地演出。除担纲演员外，他更担当幕后工作，期间更学习舞台化妆及布景灯光等，自此建立对演艺事业的兴趣。\n\n　　1936年与李洁莹结婚，婚后二人育有四子两女。\n\n　　1940年懂化妆技巧的石坚正式投身演艺圈，起初曾为有“万能泰斗”之称的已故粤剧老倌薛觉先担任化妆师。该年石坚正式成为电影演员，在首部有份拍摄的间谍片《血海花》中扮演日本特务。\n\n　　1949年获导演胡鹏邀请拍摄《黄飞鸿传》，于第一部黄飞鸿影片《鞭风灭烛》饰演黄飞鸿对头人角色，尽显反派本色，自此奠定“奸人坚”地位。在首二十年的电影生涯中，石坚多数被委以担当反派角色。当中最经典的除了《黄飞鸿》中的奸人坚外，于“如来神掌”中的天残脚，“方世玉”的对头人角色更是脍炙人口。其让人不寒而栗的招牌邪笑声更经常为后来电影中不少演员所仿效。1973年 ，更在李小龙电影《龙争虎斗》中，饰演大反派“韩先生”角色，石坚在片中尽显其武术功架，将北派武功呈现观众眼前，当中与李小龙的对垒更是精彩连连。\n\n　　1975年进入无线电视担当艺员，《功夫热》为首部参与的电视剧，之后拍摄过《狂潮》、《倚天屠龙记》、《射雕英雄传之东邪西毒》等经典剧作。与电影时期相反，石坚在电视剧中大多饰演儒雅谦逊的慈祥长辈角色，尽显其真性情，例子包括《网中人》中的“龙冠三”、《亲情》中的“苏大鹏”、《流氓大亨》中的外公等。\n\n　　1980年代初获邀接拍利口乐薄荷糖广告，为品牌成功塑造出个人形象，深入民心。\n\n　　1992年石坚退出影坛，其现时最后一部影视作品，为专为石坚度身订造开拍的电影奸人世家，于1994年公演。\n\n　　2007年1月至2月，香港电影资料馆举行“点止奸人咁简单——石坚”节目，放映十三出石坚成名电影作品。\n\n　　2009年6月3日下午4时33分在伊利沙伯医院因心脏衰竭逝世，享寿97岁。","name":"石坚","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"석견","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"石堅（1913 年 1 月 1 日－2009 年 6 月 3 日），原名石榮璋，籍貫廣東番禺石崗村，香港粵語電影演員，電影、電視作品無數。另有外號奸人堅，是粵語電影中的老牌反派，經常都在黃飛鴻電影裏擔任反派的角色。\n\n石堅從小被二媽養大，少年時體弱多病，故習武以強身健體，一學九年，習鷹爪、螳螂、羅漢、少林、山西朝元派和保定快跤等門派功夫，因此建立起功夫底子，為日後的演藝生涯豎立基礎。適逢抗日戰爭爆發，學生時期的石堅積極投入罷課抗戰，聯袂友人籌劃抗日話劇，縱橫省港兩地演出。除擔綱演員外，他更擔當幕後工作，期間更學習舞台化妝 妝 妝 妝及佈景燈光等，自此建立對演藝事業的興趣。\n\n1936 年與李潔瑩結婚，婚後二人育有四子兩女。\n\n1940 年懂化妝 妝 妝 妝技巧的石堅正式投身演藝圈，起初曾為有“萬能泰鬥”之稱的已故粵劇老倌薛覺先擔任化妝 妝 妝 妝師。該年石堅正式成為電影演員，在首部有份拍攝的間諜片《血海花》中扮演日本特務。\n\n1949 年獲導演胡鵬邀請拍攝《黃飛鴻傳》，於第一部黃飛鴻影片《鞭風滅燭》飾演黃飛鴻對頭人角色，盡顯反派本色，自此奠定“奸人堅”地位。在首二十年的電影生涯中，石堅多數被委以擔當反派角色。當中最經典的除了《黃飛鴻》中的奸人堅外，於“如來神掌”中的天殘腳，“方世玉”的對頭人角色更是膾炙人口。其讓人不寒而栗的招牌邪笑聲更經常為後來電影中不少演員所仿效。1973 年 ，更在李小龍電影《龍爭虎鬥》中，飾演大反派“韓先生”角色，石堅在片中盡顯其武術功架，將北派武功呈現觀眾眼前，當中與李小龍的對壘更是精彩聯聯。\n\n1975 年進入無線電視擔當藝員，《功夫熱》為首部參與的電視劇，之後拍攝過《狂潮》、《倚天屠龍記》、《射鵰英雄傳之東邪西毒》等經典劇作。與電影時期相反，石堅在電視劇中大多飾演儒雅謙遜的慈祥長輩角色，盡顯其真性情，例子包括《網中人》中的“龍冠三”、《親情》中的“蘇大鵬”、《流氓大亨》中的外公等。\n\n1980 年代初獲邀接拍利口樂薄荷糖廣告，為品牌成功塑造出個人形象，深入民心。\n\n1992 年石堅退出影壇，其現時最後一部影視作品，為專為石堅度身訂造開拍的電影奸人世家，於 1994 年公演。\n\n2007 年 1 月至 2 月，香港電影資料館舉行“點止奸人咁簡單——石堅”節目，放映十三出石堅成名電影作品。\n\n2009 年 6 月 3 日下午 4 時 33 分在伊利沙伯醫院因心臟衰竭逝世，享壽 97 歲。","name":"石堅","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"PL","iso_639_1":"pl","name":"Polski","english_name":"Polish","data":{"biography":"Shih Kien (chiń. 石堅, 1 stycznia 1913 – 3 czerwca 2009), znany również jako Shek Wing-cheung, Sek Gin lub Shek Kin, był chińskim aktorem i mistrzem sztuk walki mieszkającym w Hongkongu. Urodził się 1 stycznia 1913 roku w Shigang w Kantonie w Chinach, a zmarł 3 czerwca 2009 roku w Hongkongu.\n\nSek Kin rozpoczął karierę w przemyśle filmowym w 1939 roku jako charakteryzator. Zadebiutował jako aktor w 1940 roku filmem „Kwiat w morzu krwi”. W latach 50. i 60. XX wieku zyskał sławę dzięki rolom czarnych charakterów w filmach kung-fu. Wystąpił w wielu popularnych filmach z tamtej epoki, w tym w seriach „Wong Fei Hung”, „Fong Sai Yuk” i „Dłoń Buddy”.\n\nW 1973 roku Sek Kin zagrał u boku Bruce'a Lee w filmie „Wejście smoka”. Wcielił się w rolę Hana, głównego czarnego charakteru w filmie. Rola Sek Kina w „Wejściu smoka” spotkała się z uznaniem krytyków, a aktor jest uważany za jednego z największych czarnych charakterów w kinie kung-fu.\n\nW latach 70. i 80. XX wieku Sek Kin kontynuował grę w filmach i serialach telewizyjnych. Zaczął również pracować jako kierownik produkcji filmowej. W 1996 roku został uhonorowany nagrodą za całokształt twórczości przyznawaną przez Stowarzyszenie Krytyków Filmowych Hongkongu. W 2003 roku otrzymał nagrodę za osiągnięcia zawodowe podczas Hong Kong Film Awards.\n\nSek Kin zmarł 3 czerwca 2009 roku w wieku 96 lat. Był cenionym aktorem, który wniósł znaczący wkład w hongkoński przemysł filmowy. Pamiętany jest za swoje kultowe role czarnych charakterów w filmach kung fu, a także za pionierską pracę w początkach kina Hongkongu.","name":"","primary":false}}]}},"person_1206317_translations":{"at":1772469963649,"data":{"id":1206317,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuki Ono","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuki Ono","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"小野友树（日语：小野 友樹／おの ゆうき Ono Yūki，1984年6月22日—），日本的男性声优。早稻田大学运动科学系毕业。血型为AB型。目前并没有隶属任何经纪公司，属于自由身。\n\n是同为声优的谷山纪章的大粉丝。当声优的最大理由正是因为想成为谷山纪章的同事。","name":"小野友树","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"오노 유키","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"小野友樹是日本的男性聲優、歌手。出身於靜岡縣，畢業於早稻田大學運動科學系。","name":"小野友樹","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"小野友樹","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuki Ono","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"ยูกิ โอโนะ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IR","iso_639_1":"fa","name":"فارسی","english_name":"Persian","data":{"biography":"","name":"یوکی اونو","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"SA","iso_639_1":"ar","name":"العربية","english_name":"Arabic","data":{"biography":"","name":"يوكي أونو","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Юки Оно","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Júki Ono","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuki Ono","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yuki Ono","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Юкі Оно","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"小野友樹，日本的男性聲優。早稻田大學運動科學系畢業。目前沒有隸屬任何經紀公司，屬於自由身。","name":"小野友樹","primary":false}}]}},"person_2453132_translations":{"at":1772469963720,"data":{"id":2453132,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Kwon Hyuk is an up-and-coming South Korean actor who was born on February 19, 1989. He starred in the 2020 thriller film “Negotiations,” as well as the drama series titles “Graceful Friends” (2020) and “A Good Supper” (2021).","name":"Kwon Hyuk","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"권혁","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"權赫","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"權赫","pr